# ============================================================================
# Debug artifacts at repo root (Phase 35-48 accumulated; never commit)
# ============================================================================
# Restricted to root with leading slash so nested docs/, claudedocs/, frontend/
# etc. are unaffected. Real assets belong under those folders, never at root.

# Screenshots & images at root
/*.png
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg

# Snapshot / debug markdown at root
/*-snap.md
/*-snapshot.md
/snapshot-*.md
/chat-area-snapshot.md
/completed-snapshot.md
/orch-*.md
/orchestrator-deep.md
/orchestrator-ready.md
/experts-*.md
/team-mode-*.md
/scrolled-*.md
/t3-*.md

# Console & inventory dumps at root
/console-*.txt
/backend_inventory_*.txt
/*-this-session-is-being-continued-*.txt

# One-off scripts at root
/extract_chunk_*.py
/graphify_chunk_*.py

# ============================================================================
# TypeScript / Vite build artifacts (regenerated on each `npm run build`)
# ============================================================================
*.tsbuildinfo
# vite.config.ts is the source; .d.ts and .js are emitted by `tsc -b` because
# tsconfig.node.json has composite=true. They regenerate, so don't track them.
/frontend/vite.config.d.ts
/frontend/vite.config.js

# ============================================================================
# Graphify outputs (local reading aid only; not committed)
# ============================================================================
# Per CLAUDE.md §graphify: graphify-out/ is a Claude Code local reading
# accelerator. INFERRED edges (~75% of graph) are LLM hypotheses, not
# facts — committing them puts unverified data in git history. Each
# `graphify update .` regenerates content; tracking would create noise
# diffs in every PR. Rebuild cost is low (manifest diff is fast).
/graphify-out/

# ============================================================================
# Local development logs (devlog) — not committed to GitHub
# ============================================================================
# docs/08-development-log/ is a local-only conversation / decision diary.
# Useful for AI assistant continuity across sessions, but the raw transcripts
# are noisy and not appropriate for shared history. Kept untracked so they
# can grow freely without polluting commits.
/docs/08-development-log/
